<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">632.006/1–2245: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-22T16:00:00-03:00">January
                                    22, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>222. Embassy’s 104, January 10, 3 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d565fn5">Not
                                printed.</note> While I was with Velloso this morning Souza Costa
                            telephoned to inform him that he will modify the import control order in
                            accordance with the Department’s desire that it be considered as a
                            temporary war measure. Furthermore that he has reduced the list as
                            reported in the Embassy’s telegram 4574, December 29, 8 p.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d565fn6">
                                <ref target="frus1944v07#pg_670">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>, p. 670</ref>.</note> He indicated
                            that the order would be put into effect shortly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>